\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 events:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Definition
Independence of a set of events.
 A list of 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 events 
\begin_inset Formula $A_{1},A_{2},\dots,A_{n}$
\end_inset

 is mutually independent if and only if for each set of 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $(2\leq k\leq n)$
\end_inset

 distinct indices 
\begin_inset Formula $i_{1},i_{2},\dots,i_{k}$
\end_inset

 which are elements of 
\begin_inset Formula $\{1,2,\dots,n\}$
\end_inset

 we have
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
P(A_{i_{1}}\cap A_{i_{2}}\cap\cdots\cap A_{i_{k}})=P(A_{i_{1}})P(A_{i_{2}})\cdots P(A_{i_{k}}).
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

