\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

) and mutually exclusive (i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $B_{i}\cap B_{j}=\emptyset$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $i\neq j$
\end_inset

) form an event space 
\begin_inset Formula $S'=\{B_{1},B_{2},\dots,B_{n}\}$
\end_inset

.
